translations: v．反对，提出异议：表示不同意或不赞成某事物。
· He kept objecting to my suggestions.

phrs.translation: 面向对象的；对象趋向的；物件导向的
被控对象，受控对象；控制对象
不成问题；不在话下；不计较
n. 直接宾语；直接客体
目标识别；对象的确认，对象标识；物体识别

sentences.sentence: Of course, when they go to college, they might start objecting to being monitored as they're on parole.
sentences.translation: 当然，当他们上了大学，他们可能会开始反对在假释期间被监视。

sentences.sentence: Two of the three objecting Justices—Samuel Alito and Clarence Thomas—agreed with this Constitutional logic but disagreed about which Arizona rules conflicted with the federal statute.
sentences.translation: 三位反对法官中的两位——塞缪尔·阿利托和克拉伦斯·托马斯——同意这一宪法逻辑，但对于亚利桑那州法律中的哪一条款触犯了联邦法律这个问题存在分歧。

sentences.sentence: Are you objecting to this one because of its shape?
sentences.translation: 你单不吃海马是不是因为它的形状？
